        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/31497",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Please note that this is not a bug.\n\nSeveral elements like File, Image or Captcha need own decorators, otherwise they could not be rendered.\nAs you deleted all default decorators and gave not the needed file decorator to the file element, the file element itself throws an exception as it can not be rendered properly.\n\nThis has been mentioned in FAQ. ( http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/wiki\/display\/ZFFAQ\/Forms )\nAlso several issues have been filled and answered in past.\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-05-30T14:51:09.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-05-30T14:51:09.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36935",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dennisatddddesigns",
                        "name": "dennisatddddesigns",
                        "displayName": "Dennis Day",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Seems to me that the file element should check to see if the decorator is using ViewHelper and give a more descriptive error message.  At least this way, people could get on the right track.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dennisatddddesigns",
                        "name": "dennisatddddesigns",
                        "displayName": "Dennis Day",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-12-15T08:01:12.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-12-15T08:01:12.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36937",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "In my opinion \"File decorator not found\/set\" is a proper error message.\r\nYou could have a file element with File and ViewHelper decorator set.\r\n\r\nThe exception was added because many people did simply not read the manual. In past there was no error at all, the file element did simply not work.\r\n\r\nAnyway:\r\nIt is mentioned within the manual at 2 places, within the FAQ, within the mailing list and also within several public places which can be found on the web.\r\n\r\nEven when the text would be changed to \"Stupid: you must add the file decorator\" there are still many people which will raise an issue instead of reading or searching first. ;-)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-12-15T08:23:51.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-12-15T08:23:51.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
    },
